element.description:
for bullets: minimum distance for scaling damage by range;
                    typically the *maximum* bullet damage occurs at this range and closer.
                    for projectiles: momentum at which damage scaling begins (scale depends on weapon, but usually
                    velocity squared);
                    typically, this is the momentum value at which the weapon does the *minimum* damage.

for bullets: maximum distance for scaling damage by range (except for extreme range);
                    typically, bullets do the *minimum* distance at this range and further.
                    for projectiles: momentum at which damage scaling ends (scale depends on weapon, but typically is
                    velocity squared);
                    typically, this is the momentum value at which the weapon does the *maximum* damage.
